description._content: Catalog #: 09_00976 Title: Colonel Cleon Eugene Freeman Special Collection Photo Date: 1945 Additional Information: Portrait of man in military uniform. Handwritten inscription ""For Cleon Freeman, with best wishes ""A True Copy"" Belgium 26 Feb 1945"", Cleon Freeman was a Captain of the 110th Air Corps Observation Squadron during World War II and served as a liason officer between the Ninth Air Force and ground forces working in England. He was awarded the Croix de Guerre in 1940 and the Bronze Star Medal in 1944, Tags: Colonel Cleon Eugene Freeman Special Collection Photo,Â 1945 Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
